ikeMonModule.description: The MIB module to describe IKE phase 1 SAs, security association suites, and entity level objects and events for those types.

ikeMonMIBObjects.name: ikeMonMIBObjects
ikeMonMIBObjects.description: This is the base object identifier for all IKE monitoring MIB branches.

ikePhase1Objects.name: ikePhase1Objects
ikePhase1Objects.description: This is the base object identifier for IKE phase 1 objects.

phase2Objects.name: phase2Objects
phase2Objects.description: This is the base object identifier for IKE phase 2 objects, including the suite and phase 2 SA tables.

oakleyObjects.name: oakleyObjects
oakleyObjects.description: This is the base object identifier for Oakley groups.

ikeGroups.name: ikeGroups
ikeGroups.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which describe the groups in this MIB.

ikeConformance.name: ikeConformance
ikeConformance.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which describe the conformance for this MIB.

ikeTables.name: ikeTables
ikeTables.description: This is the base object identifier for the IKE phase 1 security associations table.

ikeGlobals.name: ikeGlobals
ikeGlobals.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which are global values for IKE.

ikeTrafStats.name: ikeTrafStats
ikeTrafStats.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which are global values for IKE.

ikeErrors.name: ikeErrors
ikeErrors.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which are global values for IKE.

ikeTrapControl.name: ikeTrapControl
ikeTrapControl.description: This is the base object identifier for all trap controls for the IKE phase 1 SA portion of this MIB.

ikeTraps.name: ikeTraps
ikeTraps.description: This is the base object identifier for all traps for the IKE phase 1 SA portion of this MIB.

ikeNotifications.name: ikeNotifications
ikeNotifications.description: This is the base object identifier for all notification objects of this MIB.

suiteTables.name: suiteTables
suiteTables.description: This is the base object identifier for the suite table.

suiteGlobals.name: suiteGlobals
suiteGlobals.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which are global values for suites.

suiteTrafStats.name: suiteTrafStats
suiteTrafStats.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which are global counters for suite traffic statistics.

suiteErrors.name: suiteErrors
suiteErrors.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which are global error counters for suites.

suiteTrapControl.name: suiteTrapControl
suiteTrapControl.description: This is the base object identifier for all trap controls for the suite portion of this MIB.

suiteTraps.name: suiteTraps
suiteTraps.description: This is the base object identifier for all traps for the suite portion of this MIB.

modpGroupTable.name: modpGroupTable
modpGroupTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing Oakley MODP groups that are not well known that the entity has negotiated or knows about. There should be one row for every Oakley MODP group negotiated or supported by the entity that is not a well- known group. The maximum number of rows is implementation dependent.

modpGroupEntry.name: modpGroupEntry
modpGroupEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the information on a particular Oakley MODP group. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

modpGroupIndex.name: modpGroupIndex
modpGroupIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each Oakley MODP group. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1. The value for each MODP group must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

modpFieldSize.name: modpFieldSize
modpFieldSize.description: The size of a field element, in bits.

modpPrime.name: modpPrime
modpPrime.description: The prime of the MODP group.

modpGenerator.name: modpGenerator
modpGenerator.description: The generator value of the MODP group.

modpLPF.name: modpLPF
modpLPF.description: The largest prime factor of the group size, or 0 if unspecified.

modpStrength.name: modpStrength
modpStrength.description: The strength of the group, which is approximately the number of key-bits protected, or 0 if unspecified.

ecpGroupTable.name: ecpGroupTable
ecpGroupTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing Oakley ECP groups that are not well known that the entity has negotiated or knows about. There should be one row for every Oakley ECP group negotiated or supported by the entity that is not a well- known group. The maximum number of rows is implementation dependent.

ecpGroupEntry.name: ecpGroupEntry
ecpGroupEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the information on a particular Oakley ECP group. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

ecpGroupIndex.name: ecpGroupIndex
ecpGroupIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each Oakley ECP group. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1. The value for each ECP group must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

ecpFieldSize.name: ecpFieldSize
ecpFieldSize.description: The size of a field element, in bits.

ecpPrime.name: ecpPrime
ecpPrime.description: The prime of the ECP group.

ecpGeneratorOne.name: ecpGeneratorOne
ecpGeneratorOne.description: The first generator value of the group.

ecpGeneratorTwo.name: ecpGeneratorTwo
ecpGeneratorTwo.description: The second generator value of the group.

ecpParameterOne.name: ecpParameterOne
ecpParameterOne.description: The first elliptic curve parameter value of the group.

ecpParameterTwo.name: ecpParameterTwo
ecpParameterTwo.description: The second elliptic curve parameter value of the group.

ecpLPF.name: ecpLPF
ecpLPF.description: The largest prime factor of the group size, or 0 if unspecified.

ecpOrder.name: ecpOrder
ecpOrder.description: The order of the group, or 0 if it is unspecified.

ecpStrength.name: ecpStrength
ecpStrength.description: The strength of the group, which is approximately the number of key-bits protected.

ec2nGroupTable.name: ec2nGroupTable
ec2nGroupTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing Oakley EC2N groups that are not well known that the entity has negotiated or knows about. There should be one row for every Oakley group negotiated or supported by the entity that is not a well-known group. The maximum number of rows is implementation dependent.

ec2nGroupEntry.name: ec2nGroupEntry
ec2nGroupEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the information on a particular Oakley EC2N group. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

ec2nGroupIndex.name: ec2nGroupIndex
ec2nGroupIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each Oakley EC2N group. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1. The value for each EC2N group must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

ec2nDegree.name: ec2nDegree
ec2nDegree.description: The degree of the irreducible polynomial.

ec2nIrrPoly.name: ec2nIrrPoly
ec2nIrrPoly.description: The prime or the irreducible field polynomial.

ec2nGeneratorOne.name: ec2nGeneratorOne
ec2nGeneratorOne.description: The first generator value of the group.

ec2nGeneratorTwo.name: ec2nGeneratorTwo
ec2nGeneratorTwo.description: The second generator value of the group.

ec2nParameterOne.name: ec2nParameterOne
ec2nParameterOne.description: The first elliptic curve parameter value of the group.

ec2nParameterTwo.name: ec2nParameterTwo
ec2nParameterTwo.description: The second elliptic curve parameter value of the group.

ec2nLPF.name: ec2nLPF
ec2nLPF.description: The largest prime factor of the group size, or 0 if unspecified.

ec2nOrder.name: ec2nOrder
ec2nOrder.description: The order of the group, or 0 if it is unspecified.

ec2nStrength.name: ec2nStrength
ec2nStrength.description: The strength of the group, which is approximately the number of key-bits protected, or 0 if it is unspecified.

ikeSaTable.name: ikeSaTable
ikeSaTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing the IKE SAs. The number of rows is the same as the number of IKE phase 2 SAs that are in the process of being negotiated or are negotiated in the entity. Phrased another way, there is a row in this table for each row in 'saTable' for which 'saDoi' is 'ipsecDOI(1)'. The maximum number of rows is implementation dependent.

ikeSaEntry.name: ikeSaEntry
ikeSaEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the information on a particular IKE SA. There is an entry in this table for each 'saEntry' in which which 'saDoi' is 'ipsecDOI(1)'. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

saAuthMethod.name: saAuthMethod
saAuthMethod.description: The authentication method used to authenticate the peers. Note that this does not include the specific method of extended authentication if extended authentication is used.

saPeerIdType.name: saPeerIdType
saPeerIdType.description: The type of ID used by the peer that negotiated this SA.

saPeerId.name: saPeerId
saPeerId.description: The ID of the used by the peer that negotiated this SA.

saPeerCertSerialNum.name: saPeerCertSerialNum
saPeerCertSerialNum.description: The serial number of the certificate of the peer this SA was negotiated with. This object has no meaning if a certificate was not used in authenticating the peer.

saPeerCertIssuer.name: saPeerCertIssuer
saPeerCertIssuer.description: The issuer name of the certificate of the peer this control channel was negotiated with. This object has no meaning if a certificate was not used in authenticating the peer.

saLocalIdType.name: saLocalIdType
saLocalIdType.description: The type of ID used by the local entity that negotiated this SA.

saLocalId.name: saLocalId
saLocalId.description: The ID of the used by the local entity that negotiated this SA.

saEncAlg.name: saEncAlg
saEncAlg.description: The encryption algorithm used to protect this SA.

saEncKeyLength.name: saEncKeyLength
saEncKeyLength.description: The length of the encryption key in bits used for the algorithm specified in the 'saEncAlg' object. It may be 0 if the key length is implicit in the specified algorithm.

saHashAlg.name: saHashAlg
saHashAlg.description: The hash algorithm used to protect this SA.

saHashKeyLength.name: saHashKeyLength
saHashKeyLength.description: The length of the encryption key in bits used for the algorithm specified in the 'saHashAlg' object. It may be 0 if the key length is implicit in the specified algorithm.

saPRF.name: saPRF
saPRF.description: The pseudo-random function used by this SA, or 0 if the HMAC version of the negotiated hash algorithm is used as a pseudo-random function.

saOakleyGroupDesc.name: saOakleyGroupDesc
saOakleyGroupDesc.description: The group number used to generate the Diffie-Hellman key pair when setting up the SA, or 0 if none of the defined groups was used. If this value is 0, the 'saOakleyGroup' must not also be OBJECT IDENTIFIER { 0 0 }.

saOakleyGroup.name: saOakleyGroup
saOakleyGroup.description: The object identifier of the Oakley group row that was used if a well-known group was not used to generate the Diffie- Hellman key pair for this SA. If a well-known group was used, the value should be set to the OBJECT IDENTIFIER { 0 0 }. For example, if the group is a MODP group, the value of this object is the object identifier of 'modpGroupIndex' of the appropriate row ('modpGroupEntry') in 'modpGroupTable'.

saLimitSeconds.name: saLimitSeconds
saLimitSeconds.description: The maximum number of seconds the SA is allowed to exist, or 0 if there is no time-based limit on the existence of the SA. The display value is limited to 4,294,967,295 seconds (more than 136 years); values greater than that value will be truncated.

saLimitKbytes.name: saLimitKbytes
saLimitKbytes.description: The maximum number of kilobytes the SA is allowed to encrypt before it expires, or 0 if there is no traffic-by- byte-based limit on the existence of the SA. The display value is limited to 4,294,967,295 kilobytes (more than 4,194,304 Mbyte ); values greater than that value will be truncated.

saLimitKeyUses.name: saLimitKeyUses
saLimitKeyUses.description: The maximum number of times the SA is allowed to provide keying material from its own Diffie-Hellman exchange before it expires, or 0 if there is no keying material-based limit on the existence of the SA.

saAccKbytes.name: saAccKbytes
saAccKbytes.description: The number of kilobytes the SA has encrypted that count against any lifetime restriction based on traffic. This value may be 0 if there is no such restriction.

saKeyUses.name: saKeyUses
saKeyUses.description: The number of times the SA is has provided keying material derived from its own original Diffie-Hellman exchange.

saCreatedSuites.name: saCreatedSuites
saCreatedSuites.description: The total number of SA suites that this SA has successfully created. In other words, the total number of successful quick mode exchanges multiplied by the number of SA payloads in each of those exchanges.

saDeletedSuites.name: saDeletedSuites
saDeletedSuites.description: The total number of SA suites that this SA has sent or received SA suite delete notifications for. When delete notifications are sent or received for more than one SA in an SA suite, this number shall be decremented by one, and not by the number SAs in the suite that were deleted.

saByCreatorsTable.name: saByCreatorsTable
saByCreatorsTable.description: The (conceptual) table that sorts the IKE phase 1 SAs by the endpoint identifiers. The number of rows in this table is the same as the number of IKE phase 1 SAs in the entity.

saByCreatorsEntry.name: saByCreatorsEntry
saByCreatorsEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) referencing a particular IKE phase 1 SA. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

saByCreatorsLocalIdType.name: saByCreatorsLocalIdType
saByCreatorsLocalIdType.description: The type of ID used by the local entity that negotiated this SA.

saByCreatorsLocalId.name: saByCreatorsLocalId
saByCreatorsLocalId.description: The ID of the used by the local entity that negotiated this SA.

saByCreatorsPeerIdType.name: saByCreatorsPeerIdType
saByCreatorsPeerIdType.description: The type of ID used by the remote entity that negotiated this SA.

saByCreatorsPeerId.name: saByCreatorsPeerId
saByCreatorsPeerId.description: The ID of the used by the remote entity that negotiated this SA.

saByCreatorsIndex.name: saByCreatorsIndex
saByCreatorsIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each IKE phase 1 SA that exists between the two endpoints. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1.

saIkeLocalIpAddress.name: saIkeLocalIpAddress
saIkeLocalIpAddress.description: The 'saLocalIpAddress' of the phase 1 SA for this row.

saIkeRemoteIpAddress.name: saIkeRemoteIpAddress
saIkeRemoteIpAddress.description: The 'saRemoteIpAddress' of the phase 1 SA for this row.

saIkeInitiatorCookie.name: saIkeInitiatorCookie
saIkeInitiatorCookie.description: The 'saInitiatorCookie' of the phase 1 SA for this row.

saIkeResponderCookie.name: saIkeResponderCookie
saIkeResponderCookie.description: The 'saResponderCookie' of the phase 1 SA for this row.

exchangeTable.name: exchangeTable
exchangeTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing the exchanges used. There should be one row for every exchange attempt that has occurred using a phase 1 security association that exists in the entity. The maximum number of rows is implementation dependent.

exchangeEntry.name: exchangeEntry
exchangeEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the information on a particular exchange used in an SA. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

exchangeType.name: exchangeType
exchangeType.description: The type of the exchange for which the statistics of this row apply.

exchangeTotalCount.name: exchangeTotalCount
exchangeTotalCount.description: The total number of complete exchanges of the type performed using the SA, as either initiator or as responder. If there were failed attempts to initiate exchanges, this value is not equal to the sum of 'exchangeInitiatedCount' and 'exchangeRespondedCount'.

exchangeInitiatedCount.name: exchangeInitiatedCount
exchangeInitiatedCount.description: The total number of exchanges of the type attempted using the SA as initiator. This includes exchange that failed or were incomplete

exchangeRespondedCount.name: exchangeRespondedCount
exchangeRespondedCount.description: The total number of complete exchanges of the type performed using the SA as responder.

suiteTable.name: suiteTable
suiteTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing the phase 2 suites. The number of rows in this table is the same as the number of suites in the entity. The maximum number of rows is implementation dependent.

suiteEntry.name: suiteEntry
suiteEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the information on a particular phase 2 SA suite. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

suiteIndex.name: suiteIndex
suiteIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each SA suite. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1.

suiteLocalAddress.name: suiteLocalAddress
suiteLocalAddress.description: The address used by the local entity that negotiated the SA suite. IPv4 entities will prefix the IP address with '0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:FFFF::'.

suiteRemoteAddress.name: suiteRemoteAddress
suiteRemoteAddress.description: The address used by the remote entity that negotiated the SA suite. IPv4 entities will prefix the IP address with '0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:FFFF::'.

suitePhase1RemoteIdType.name: suitePhase1RemoteIdType
suitePhase1RemoteIdType.description: The type of ID used by the remote entity that negotiated this suite.

suitePhase1RemoteId.name: suitePhase1RemoteId
suitePhase1RemoteId.description: The ID of the remote entity that negotiated this suite.

suitePhase1LocalIdType.name: suitePhase1LocalIdType
suitePhase1LocalIdType.description: The type of ID used by the local entity that negotiated this suite.

suitePhase1LocalId.name: suitePhase1LocalId
suitePhase1LocalId.description: The ID of the local entity that negotiated this suite.

suiteRemoteId.name: suiteRemoteId
suiteRemoteId.description: The remote identifier of the SAs in the suite. It may be 0 if unknown or if the suite uses transport mode encapsulation. This corresponds to the destination identifier of outbound SAs in the suite, and to the source identifier of inbound SAs in the suite. This value is taken directly from the optional ID payloads that are exchanged during phase 2 negotiations.

suiteRemoteIdType.name: suiteRemoteIdType
suiteRemoteIdType.description: The type of ID used for 'suiteRemoteId'. It may be 0 if unknown or if the suite uses transport mode encapsulation. This value is taken directly from the optional ID payloads that are exchanged during phase 2 negotiations.

suiteLocalId.name: suiteLocalId
suiteLocalId.description: The local identifier of the SAs in the suite. It may be 0 if unknown or if the suite uses transport mode encapsulation. This corresponds to the source identifier of outbound SAs in the suite, and to the destination identifier of inbound SAs in the suite. This value is taken directly from the optional ID payloads that are exchanged during phase 2 negotiations.

suiteLocalIdType.name: suiteLocalIdType
suiteLocalIdType.description: The type of ID used for 'suiteLocalId'. It may be 0 if unknown or if the suite uses transport mode encapsulation. This value is taken directly from the optional ID payloads that are exchanged during phase 2 negotiations.

suiteProtocol.name: suiteProtocol
suiteProtocol.description: The transport-layer protocol number that this suite carries, or 0 if it carries any protocol. This value is taken directly from the optional ID payloads that are exchanged during phase 2 negotiations.

suiteRemotePort.name: suiteRemotePort
suiteRemotePort.description: The remote port number of the protocol that this suite carries, or 0 if it carries any port number. This corresponds to the destination port number of outbound SAs in the suite, and to the source port number of inbound SAs in the suite. This value is taken directly from the optional ID payloads that are exchanged during phase 2 negotiations.

suiteLocalPort.name: suiteLocalPort
suiteLocalPort.description: The local port number of the protocol that this SA carries, or 0 if it carries any port number. This corresponds to the source port number of outbound SAs in the suite, and to the destination port number of inbound SAs in the suite. This value is taken directly from the optional ID payloads that are exchanged during phase 2 negotiations

suiteOakleyGroupDesc.name: suiteOakleyGroupDesc
suiteOakleyGroupDesc.description: The group number used to generate the Diffie-Hellman key pair when setting up the SA, or 0 if none of the well known groups was used, or if perfect forward secrecy was not used.

suiteOakleyGroup.name: suiteOakleyGroup
suiteOakleyGroup.description: The table index value of the Oakley group row that was used if a well-known group was not used to generate the Diffie- Hellman key pair for this SA. If a well-known group was used, or if perfect forward secrecy was not used, the value should be set to the OBJECT IDENTIFIER { 0 0 }.

suiteLifeSeconds.name: suiteLifeSeconds
suiteLifeSeconds.description: The number of seconds that the SA has existed.

suiteInUserOctets.name: suiteInUserOctets
suiteInUserOctets.description: The amount of user level traffic measured in bytes handled by the suite in the inbound direction. This is the same as the user level traffic of the inner most inbound SA in the suite. Note that if the inner-most SA is a shared IPcomp SA, then this value may be difficult to calculate.

suiteInPackets.name: suiteInPackets
suiteInPackets.description: The number of inbound packets handled by the suite. This is the same as the number of packets handled by any one of the inbound SAs in the suite.

suiteOutUserOctets.name: suiteOutUserOctets
suiteOutUserOctets.description: The amount of user level traffic measured in bytes handled by the suite in the outbound direction. This is the same as the user level traffic of the inner most outbound SA in the suite. Note that if the inner most SA is a shared IPcomp SA, then this value may be difficult to calculate.

suiteOutPackets.name: suiteOutPackets
suiteOutPackets.description: The number of outbound packets handled by the suite. This is the same as the number of packets handled by any one of the outbound SAs in the suite.

suiteSendErrors.name: suiteSendErrors
suiteSendErrors.description: The number of outbound packets discarded by the suite due to any error. This is the same as the sum of all errors of all outbound SAs in the suite.

suiteReceiveErrors.name: suiteReceiveErrors
suiteReceiveErrors.description: The number of inbound packets discarded by the suite due to any error. This is the same as the sum of all errors of all inbound SAs in the suite.

phase2SaTable.name: phase2SaTable
phase2SaTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing ID information for the phase 2 SAs that are part of suites. The number of rows in this table is the same as the number of unidirectional phase 2 IPsec SA pairs that are created as part of suites. The maximum number of rows is implementation dependent.

phase2SaEntry.name: phase2SaEntry
phase2SaEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the information on a particular phase 2 SA within a suite. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

saOrder.name: saOrder
saOrder.description: The position within the suite of the pair of SAs indicated by this row. A value of 1 is used to represent the outer-most SA pair. The outer-most SA of any given packet has its header next to the outer IP header of the processed packet, while the inner-most SA has its header nearest the data of the unprocessed packet. (Note that the IPcomp header may be missing in actual usage if a particular packet was not compressed.) This value should be monotonically increasing for every SA pair in a suite. The maximum value is implementation dependent, but will generally not exceed three.

saProtocol.name: saProtocol
saProtocol.description: The protocol of the inbound/outbound SA pair indicated by this row of the table.

saInSpi.name: saInSpi
saInSpi.description: The security parameters index of the inbound SA of the inbound/outbound SA pair. If the protocol of the SA pair is IPcomp, this value is the CPI. This value is used with the value of 'suiteLocalAddress' from the row indexed by 'suiteIndex' to create a SPI/address pair that uniquely identifies the inbound SA used in this SA suite. This can then be used to look up the SA in the appropriate inbound SA table, based on 'saProtocol'.

saOutSpi.name: saOutSpi
saOutSpi.description: The security parameters index of the outbound SA of the inbound/outbound SA pair. If the protocol of the SA pair is IPcomp, this value is the CPI. This value is used with the value of 'suiteLocalAddress' from the row indexed by 'suiteIndex' to create a SPI/address pair that uniquely identifies the outbound SA used in this SA suite. This can then be used to look up the SA in the appropriate outbound SA table, based on 'saProtocol'.

suiteByCreatorsTable.name: suiteByCreatorsTable
suiteByCreatorsTable.description: The (conceptual) table that sorts the SA suites by the endpoint identifiers. The number of rows in this table is the same as the number of suites in the entity.

suiteByCreatorsEntry.name: suiteByCreatorsEntry
suiteByCreatorsEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) referencing a particular suite. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

suiteByCreatorsP1LocalIdType.name: suiteByCreatorsP1LocalIdType
suiteByCreatorsP1LocalIdType.description: The type of ID used by the local entity that negotiated this suite.

suiteByCreatorsP1LocalId.name: suiteByCreatorsP1LocalId
suiteByCreatorsP1LocalId.description: The ID of the local entity that negotiated this suite.

suiteByCreatorsP1RemoteIdType.name: suiteByCreatorsP1RemoteIdType
suiteByCreatorsP1RemoteIdType.description: The type of ID used by the remote entity that negotiated this suite.

suiteByCreatorsP1RemoteId.name: suiteByCreatorsP1RemoteId
suiteByCreatorsP1RemoteId.description: The ID of the remote entity that negotiated this suite.

suiteByCreatorsIndex.name: suiteByCreatorsIndex
suiteByCreatorsIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each SA suite that is between the two endpoints. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1 for each SA suite between the two endpoints.

suiteByCreatorsRef.name: suiteByCreatorsRef
suiteByCreatorsRef.description: The value of 'suiteIndex' in the row ('suiteEntry') of the 'suiteTable' to which this row refers.

suiteBySelectorsTable.name: suiteBySelectorsTable
suiteBySelectorsTable.description: The (conceptual) table that sorts the suites by the selectors. The number of rows in this table is the same as the number of suites in the entity.

suiteBySelectorsEntry.name: suiteBySelectorsEntry
suiteBySelectorsEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) referencing a particular suite. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

suiteBySelectorsLocalId.name: suiteBySelectorsLocalId
suiteBySelectorsLocalId.description: The local identifier of the selector of the suite. This value is taken directly from the optional ID payloads that are exchanged during phase 2 negotiations.

suiteBySelectorsLocalIdType.name: suiteBySelectorsLocalIdType
suiteBySelectorsLocalIdType.description: The type of ID used for 'suiteBySelectorsLocalId'. This value is taken directly from the optional ID payloads that are exchanged during phase 2 negotiations.

suiteBySelectorsRemoteId.name: suiteBySelectorsRemoteId
suiteBySelectorsRemoteId.description: The remote identifier of the selector of the suite. This value is taken directly from the optional ID payloads that are exchanged during phase 2 negotiations.

suiteBySelectorsRemoteIdType.name: suiteBySelectorsRemoteIdType
suiteBySelectorsRemoteIdType.description: The type of ID used for 'suiteBySelectorsRemoteId'. This value is taken directly from the optional ID payloads that are exchanged during phase 2 negotiations.

suiteBySelectorsProtocol.name: suiteBySelectorsProtocol
suiteBySelectorsProtocol.description: The transport-layer protocol number that this suite carries, or 0 if it carries any protocol. This value is taken directly from the optional ID payloads that are exchanged during phase 2 negotiations.

suiteBySelectorsLocalPort.name: suiteBySelectorsLocalPort
suiteBySelectorsLocalPort.description: The local port number of the protocol that this suite carries, or 0 if it carries any port number. This value is taken directly from the optional ID payloads that are exchanged during phase 2 negotiations.

suiteBySelectorsRemotePort.name: suiteBySelectorsRemotePort
suiteBySelectorsRemotePort.description: The remote port number of the protocol that this SA carries, or 0 if it carries any port number. This value is taken directly from the optional ID payloads that are exchanged during phase 2 negotiations

suiteBySelectorsIndex.name: suiteBySelectorsIndex
suiteBySelectorsIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each SA suite that the same selectors. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1.

suiteBySelectorsRef.name: suiteBySelectorsRef
suiteBySelectorsRef.description: The value of 'suiteIndex' in the row ('suiteEntry') of the 'suiteTable' to which this row refers.

ipsecSaInSuiteTable.name: ipsecSaInSuiteTable
ipsecSaInSuiteTable.description: The (conceptual) table that allows determination of which suite a particular phase 2 SA is in. The number of rows in this table is the same as the number of phase 2 SAs in the entity.

ipsecSaInSuiteEntry.name: ipsecSaInSuiteEntry
ipsecSaInSuiteEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) referencing a particular phase 2 SA. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

ipsecSaInSuiteDestAddress.name: ipsecSaInSuiteDestAddress
ipsecSaInSuiteDestAddress.description: The destination address of the IPsec phase 2 SA to which this row refers.

ipsecSaInSuiteProtocol.name: ipsecSaInSuiteProtocol
ipsecSaInSuiteProtocol.description: The security protocol of the IPsec phase 2 SA to which this row refers.

ipsecSaInSuiteSpi.name: ipsecSaInSuiteSpi
ipsecSaInSuiteSpi.description: The SPI value of the IPsec phase 2 SA to which this row refers. If the value of 'ipsecSaInSuiteProtocol' is 'protoIpcomp(4)', then this is the CPI of the SA.

ipsecSaInSuiteRef.name: ipsecSaInSuiteRef
ipsecSaInSuiteRef.description: The value of 'suiteIndex' in the row ('suiteEntry') of the 'suiteTable' to which this row refers. This is the suite that uses this SA.

notifyCountTable.name: notifyCountTable
notifyCountTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing information on IPSec notify message counts. Rows are created in this table for every notification type that has been sent or received by the entity. This table MAY be sparsely populated; that is, rows for which the count is 0 may be absent.

notifyCountEntry.name: notifyCountEntry
notifyCountEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the total number of occurrences of a notify message. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

notifyProtocol.name: notifyProtocol
notifyProtocol.description: The value representing a protocol for which the notify was used.

notifyType.name: notifyType
notifyType.description: The value representing a specific ISAKMP notify message, or 0 if unknown. Values are assigned from the set of notify message types as defined in Section 3.14.1 of [ISAKMP], and enhanced by the IPsec DOI. In addition, the value 0 may be used for this object when the object is used as a trap cause, and the cause is unknown.

notifySentCount.name: notifySentCount
notifySentCount.description: The total number of times the specific notify message has been sent by the entity since system boot.

notifyReceivedCount.name: notifyReceivedCount
notifyReceivedCount.description: The total number of times the specific notify message has been received by the entity since system boot.

ikeCurrentSAs.name: ikeCurrentSAs
ikeCurrentSAs.description: The current number of IKE SAs in the entity.

ikeCurrentInitiatedSAs.name: ikeCurrentInitiatedSAs
ikeCurrentInitiatedSAs.description: The current number of IKE SAs successfully negotiated in the entity that were initiated by the entity.

ikeCurrentRespondedSAs.name: ikeCurrentRespondedSAs
ikeCurrentRespondedSAs.description: The current number of IKE SAs successfully negotiated in the entity that were initiated by the peer entity.

ikeTotalSAs.name: ikeTotalSAs
ikeTotalSAs.description: The total number of IKE SAs successfully negotiated in the entity since boot time.

ikeTotalInitiatedSAs.name: ikeTotalInitiatedSAs
ikeTotalInitiatedSAs.description: The total number of IKE SAs successfully negotiated in the entity since boot time that were initiated by the entity.

ikeTotalRespondedSAs.name: ikeTotalRespondedSAs
ikeTotalRespondedSAs.description: The total number of IKE SAs successfully negotiated in the entity since boot time that were initiated by the peer entity.

ikeTotalAttempts.name: ikeTotalAttempts
ikeTotalAttempts.description: The total number of IKE SAs negotiation attempts made since boot time. This includes successful negotiations.

ikeTotalSaInitAttempts.name: ikeTotalSaInitAttempts
ikeTotalSaInitAttempts.description: The total number of IKE SAs negotiation attempts made where the entity was the initiator since boot time. This includes successful negotiations.

ikeTotalSaRespAttempts.name: ikeTotalSaRespAttempts
ikeTotalSaRespAttempts.description: The total number of IKE SAs negotiation attempts made where the entity was the responder since boot time. This includes successful negotiations.

ikeTotalInPackets.name: ikeTotalInPackets
ikeTotalInPackets.description: The total number of IKE packets received by the entity since boot time, including re-transmissions and un-encrypted packets.

ikeTotalOutPackets.name: ikeTotalOutPackets
ikeTotalOutPackets.description: The total number of IKE packets sent by the entity since boot time, including re-transmissions and un-encrypted packets.

ikeTotalInOctets.name: ikeTotalInOctets
ikeTotalInOctets.description: The total amount of IKE traffic received by the entity since boot time, measured in bytes, including any re- transmitted packets received, and including encrypted and un-encrypted packets.

ikeTotalOutOctets.name: ikeTotalOutOctets
ikeTotalOutOctets.description: The total amount of IKE traffic sent by the entity since boot time, measured in bytes, including any re-transmissions and including encrypted and un-encrypted packets.

ikeTotalInitFailures.name: ikeTotalInitFailures
ikeTotalInitFailures.description: The total number of attempts to initiate an IKE phase 1 SA that failed since boot time, when there was a response from the peer entity. This value may be used to detect clogging or denial-of- service attacks.

ikeTotalInitNoResponses.name: ikeTotalInitNoResponses
ikeTotalInitNoResponses.description: The total number of attempts to initiate an IKE phase 1 SA that failed since boot time, when there was no response from the peer entity. This should only be incremented if the peer does not repond to the first packet of attempted negotiations.

ikeTotalRespFailures.name: ikeTotalRespFailures
ikeTotalRespFailures.description: The total number of attempts to initiate an IKE phase 1 SA that failed since boot time, when the initiation attempt came for the peer entity.

totalSuites.name: totalSuites
totalSuites.description: The total number of suites created by the entity since system boot.

currentSuites.name: currentSuites
currentSuites.description: The total number of suites currently in existence in the entity.

suiteTotalInUserKbytes.name: suiteTotalInUserKbytes
suiteTotalInUserKbytes.description: The total amount of user level traffic carried by all suites in the entity since boot time, measured in kilobytes, in the inbound direction. This is the sum of the 'suiteInUserOctets' column for all suite rows created since boot time.

suiteTotalInPackets.name: suiteTotalInPackets
suiteTotalInPackets.description: The total number of packets carried by all suites in the entity since boot time in the inbound direction. This is the sum of the 'suiteInPackets' column for all suite rows created since boot time.

suiteTotalOutUserKbytes.name: suiteTotalOutUserKbytes
suiteTotalOutUserKbytes.description: The total amount of user level traffic carried by all suites in the entity since boot time, measured in kilobytes, in the outbound direction. This is the sum of the 'suiteOutUserOctets' column for all suite rows created since boot time.

suiteTotalOutPackets.name: suiteTotalOutPackets
suiteTotalOutPackets.description: The total number of packets carried by all suites in the entity since boot time, in the outbound direction. This is the sum of the 'suiteOutPackets' column for all suite rows created since boot time.

suiteInitFailures.name: suiteInitFailures
suiteInitFailures.description: The total number of attempts to initiate an suite that failed since boot time, when the attempt was initiated locally.

suiteRespondFailures.name: suiteRespondFailures
suiteRespondFailures.description: The total number of attempts to initiate an suite that failed since boot time, when the attempt was initiated by the peer entity.

ikeNegFailureTrapEnable.name: ikeNegFailureTrapEnable
ikeNegFailureTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether ikeNegFailure traps should be generated.

ikeNegFailure.name: ikeNegFailure
ikeNegFailure.description: An attempt to negotiate a phase 1 IKE SA failed. The notification type sent or received is also sent as part of the trap, along with the current value of the total negotiation error counters for ISAKMP.

suiteNegFailureTrapEnable.name: suiteNegFailureTrapEnable
suiteNegFailureTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether 'suiteNegFailure' traps should be generated.

suiteNegFailure.name: suiteNegFailure
suiteNegFailure.description: An attempt to negotiate a phase 2 SA suite for the specified selectors failed. The current total failure counts are passed as well as the notification type sent or received as part of the failure.
